11	Reconciliation (United States Congress) - Wikipedia	The process was created by the Congressional Budget Act of 1974 and was first  used in 1980. Reconciliation rules allow budget related adjustments, but larger  policy changes that are extraneous to the budget are limited by "Byrd Rule", an  amendment named after Democratic Senator Robert Byrd that was passed in  1990.	https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reconciliation_(United_States_Congress)
